As the originator of XSCALE, Pete's been involved in generating several successful [[Agile Transformation]]s and innovations in Agile [[Product Management]], [[Portfolio Management|Consensus Decision-Making]] and [[Change Management|Self-Organizing Transformation]]. Pete invented the first Agile training game, contributed to early Agile books, test frameworks and project-wiki engines, and took part in the formation of the original Alliance.

Pete's working on the first [[XSCALE Book]], which includes a lot of material from this wiki, and if that's not far out enough he has gone beta with something called {{The Agile Tao}} ... You can reach Pete <a href="mailto:peter.merel@xscalealliance.org">here</a>. In real life Pete does not talk about himself in the third person ...